
[1]disperse

   DISPERSE, v.t. dispers. [L., to scatter.]

   1. To scatter; to drive asunder; to cause to separate into different
   parts; as, the Jews are dispersed among all nations.

   2. To diffuse; to spread.

   The lips of the wise disperse knowledge. Proverbs 15.

   3. To dissipate; as, the fog or the cloud is dispersed.

   4. To distribute.

                           DISPERSE, v.i. dispers.

   1. To be scattered; to separate; to go or move into different parts;
   as, the company dispersed at ten oclock.

   2. To be scattered; to vanish; as fog or vapors.
